5000|$|Despite {{claims in}} the press that local councils are {{conducting}} over a thousand RIPA-based covert surveillance operations every month for petty offences such as under-age smoking and breaches of planning regulations, the Office of Surveillance Commissioners' last report shows that public bodies granted 8,477 requests for Directed Surveillance, down over 1,400 on the previous year. Less {{than half of those}} were granted by Local Authorities, and the commissioner reported that, [...] "Generally speaking, local authorities use their powers sparingly with over half of them granting five or fewer <b>authorisations</b> <b>for</b> directed surveillance. Some sixteen per cent granted none at all." ...|$|R
